# Files consumed by the Linux host must keep LF endings regardless of who committed them.
# This repo is developed on Windows, where core.autocrlf hands out CRLF working copies —
# and a CRLF checkout breaks these silently at the worst moment: a shebang followed by \r
# fails with "bad interpreter: /bin/sh^M", and sysctl.d parses the trailing \r into the
# value. Normalising here means it cannot depend on a contributor's local git config.
*.sh text eol=lf
deploy/sysctl/*.conf text eol=lf
